==English==

===Etymology===
From [[hook]] + [[-ed]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-hooked.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''hooked'''
#Possessing a [[sharp]] [[curve]] at the end.  Resembling a [[hook]].
#[[addicted|Addicted]]; unable to [[resist]] or [[cease]].
#:''He will never leave her because he is '''hooked''' on her chocolate chip cookies.''


===Verb===
'''hooked'''
#To be caught on a hook.
#:''He '''hooked''' a fish on his first cast.''